Subject: [PATCH] subsystem: Fix when GYP crashes on standard FreeBSD7.x and
 FreeBSD8.x builds

issue: https://github.com/joyent/node/issues/6640

Fix provided by @@tjfontaine
---
 configure | 3 +++
 1 file changed, 3 insertions(+)

diff --git a/configure b/configure
index 4a38c70..83dbba7 100755
--- a/configure
+++ b/configure
@@ -706,4 +706,7 @@ elif flavor == 'win':
 else:
   gyp_args = ['-f', 'make-' + flavor]
 
+if flavor in ('freebsd'):
+  gyp_args.append('--no-parallel')
+
 subprocess.call([sys.executable, 'tools/gyp_node.py'] + gyp_args)
